"title": "2015: Jesus Christ, compassion of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2015: jesus christ, compassion of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ's pity and loving concern for the lowly and the needy. His words and deeds show God's merciful and gracious nature in action.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ shows the compassion of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:3\">2CO 1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:15\">2CH 36:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:15\">PSA 86:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:4\">HOS 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:8-Hos11:9\">HOS 11:8–11:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:72\">LUK 1:72</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:78\">LUK 1:78</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:20\">LUK 15:20</a></p>\n<h2>The compassion of Jesus Christ is the basis of Christian confidence</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:14–4:16</a></strong> <em>The Greek word here translated “sympathise” has the sense of “be compassionate towards”.</em></p>\n<h2>The demonstration of Jesus Christ's compassion</h2>\n<h3>In supporting the weak</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:20\">MAT 12:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:3\">ISA 42:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:14\">MAT 19:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:14\">MRK 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:16\">LUK 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>In healing the sick</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:14\">MAT 14:14</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:11\">LUK 9:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:34\">MAT 20:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:52\">MRK 10:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:42-Luke18:43\">LUK 18:42–18:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:41\">MRK 1:41</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:3\">MAT 8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:13\">LUK 5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:12\">LUK 13:12</a></p>\n<h3>In comforting the bereaved</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:13\">LUK 7:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:50\">LUK 8:50</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:36\">MRK 5:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:33-John11:35\">JHN 11:33–11:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:25-John19:27\">JHN 19:25–19:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:14-John20:16\">JHN 20:14–20:16</a></p>\n<h3>In feeding the hungry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:32\">MAT 15:32</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:2-Mark8:3\">MRK 8:2–8:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:16\">MAT 14:16</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:37\">MRK 6:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:13\">LUK 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:5-John6:6\">JHN 6:5–6:6</a></p>\n<h3>In finding and forgiving lost sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:36\">MAT 9:36</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:34\">MRK 6:34</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:14\">MAT 18:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:37-Matt23:38\">MAT 23:37–23:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:34-Luke13:35\">LUK 13:34–13:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:47-Luke7:48\">LUK 7:47–7:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:10-John8:11\">JHN 8:10–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>In giving rest to those who are burdened or abandoned</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28-Matt11:29\">MAT 11:28–11:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:41\">MRK 1:40–1:41</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:1-Matt8:3\">MAT 8:1–8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:13\">LUK 5:12–5:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:46\">LUK 11:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1-Luke15:2\">LUK 15:1–15:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:12-Luke17:14\">LUK 17:12–17:14</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's compassion is a model for Christians to follow</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:36-Luke10:37\">LUK 10:36–10:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:34\">JHN 13:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:18\">JHN 17:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:1\">PHP 2:1</a></p>",
